{
  "texts": [
    "The matrix cells are the intersections where we reflect on how the particular individual(s) would be affected by the particular action.",
    "These effects are represented as pros (with a plus sign) or cons (with a minus sign) and a probability level (with H for High, M for Medium, and L for Low).",
    "Table 1 shows an example of this matrix as a start for the assignment described in this paper.Different ethical theories can be used to develop the autonomy matrix, as explained in the textbook [24].",
    "In the course, we chose several.",
    "Consequentialism is the theory that students may be quicker to understand, as they have experienced this approach of looking at who is affected by what actions."
  ]
}